  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. A mesh independence verification activity was executed and its outcomes are discussed in the validation narrative; however, the evidence artefact was inadvertently linked to the solver-verification activity rather than to the mesh-independence activity, leaving the mesh-independence activity without a direct evidence provenance link.",
